<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for insert and extract a OLE object in a PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to insert and open a OLE Object in PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Add new OLE Object into a PowerPoint slide.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Extract a embedded OLE Object data.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Gets the file path of a linked OLE Object.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Gets the file name of a OLE Object.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph><Bold>Note:</Bold> This library supports creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>

